cs.GR, cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.NI, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper focuses on developing an application for interactive visualization, which falls under the graphics subfield. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the implementation of a parallel visualization application for commodity-based clusters, which falls under the distributed and parallel computing subfield. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the implementation of a software application for visualization, which falls under the mathematical software subfield. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of MPI and network bandwidth in the implementation of the parallel visualization application, which falls under the networking and internet architecture subfield. 
- cs.SC (Scientific Computing): The paper discusses the performance measurements and benchmarking of the visualization application, which falls under the scientific computing subfield.
